      </ol>

      <h3>Rate Limits</h3>
      <p>To ensure fair usage and system stability, we implement the following rate limits:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Free tier:</strong> 1,000 requests per hour</li>
        <li><strong>Pro tier:</strong> 10,000 requests per hour</li>
        <li><strong>Enterprise tier:</strong> Unlimited requests</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        If you exceed your rate limit, you'll receive a <code>429 Too Many Requests</code> response. 
        The response will include a <code>Retry-After</code> header indicating when you can retry.
      </p>

      <h3>Error Handling</h3>
      <p>Our API uses standard HTTP status codes to indicate success or failure:</p>

      <pre><code>try &#123;
  const result = await api.createResource(data);
  console.log('Success:', result);
&#125; catch (error) &#123;
  if (error.status === 400) &#123;
    console.error('Bad request:', error.message);
  &#125; else if (error.status === 401) &#123;
    console.error('Unauthorized:', error.message);
  &#125; else if (error.status === 429) &#123;
    console.error('Rate limited:', error.message);
  &#125; else &#123;
    console.error('Unexpected error:', error);
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

